  <h2>What is prompt scripting?</h2>
  <p>If you've already seen the <strong>possibility</strong>, you already know what you <strong>want</strong> it to be.</p>
  <div class="examples">
    <div>
      <h3>Write scripts to embed LLM context in the middle of your markdown docs.</h3>
      <pre>
<code>
  # Overview

  Here's the structure of the codebase:
  
  @run [tree --gitignore]  
</code>
      </pre>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>Chain LLM requests and responses like you'd pipe shell commands</h3>
      <pre>
<code>
@text tests = @run [npm test]

@text res = @run [oneshot "What's broken here? {{tests}}"]

@run [oneshot "Make a plan to fix {{res}}"]

–--

"Here's a plan to fix the failing tests."
</code>
    </pre>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>Use imports and treat markdown doc sections like modules</h3>
      <pre>
<code>
  @import [roles] from [roles.mld]


  @text infra = @embed [TESTING.md # Infrastructure]
  
  @text prompt = [[
    Read our docs: {{infra}} {{standards}}
    Review this set of changes: {{diff}}
    Please create a list of the tests we
    should add to cover the changes.
  ]]
  
  @run [oneshot {{prompt}} --system {{roles.architect}}]

  –--

  "Here's a list of the tests to add…"  
</code>
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
